                <head>No. 52.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Trail</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 25, 1887</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 51.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In view of a communication of the 21st instant
                    from Mr. E. R. Bacon, of the American Telegraph and Cable Company, you were
                    telegraphed on the 23d instant as follows: “Use good offices for extending
                    concessions to Pedro Segundo American Cable Company.”</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
